sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant B as Browser
  participant M as middleware.ts<br/>(edge gate)
  participant A as Server Action<br/>(actions/checktudo.ts)
  participant DB as Azure SQL<br/>(carros_ativos_db)

  Note over B,M: Every route except /login + /register requires a session
  B->>M: request /checktudo
  M->>M: verify dc_session cookie<br/>(HMAC via AUTH_SECRET)
  alt no / invalid session
    M-->>B: 302 /login
  else valid session on /login|/register
    M-->>B: 302 /precos
  end

  Note over B,DB: Login (invite-gated registration is analogous)
  B->>A: POST login (email, senha)
  A->>DB: SELECT users WHERE email=@e
  A->>A: scrypt verify (timing-safe)
  A-->>B: Set-Cookie dc_session (signed httpOnly) → /precos

  Note over B,DB: A consult — owner-scoped, Master reads all
  B->>A: consultar placa (Checa Tudo)
  A->>A: requireScope() → {userId, master}
  A->>DB: findFreshByPlaca(placa, product,<br/>master ? null : userId)
  alt cache HIT (own row, or any row if Master)
    DB-->>A: cached consult (incl. recall verdict)
    A-->>B: render (no vendor call)
  else MISS
    A->>A: vendor call + recall verdict
    A->>DB: INSERT owner_id = userId
    A-->>B: render
  end
  Note over A,DB: Master drops "WHERE owner_id = @owner" for reads<br/>(incl. legacy owner_id=NULL). Writes always record the acting user.
